<subSubSection id="CBA7C4D575489858B7BEFF00FED1FD18" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="description">
<paragraph id="8302975E75489858B7BEFF00FEECFEA3" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B7BEFF00FE9CFF2C" bold="true" box="[151,297,151,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Description.</emphasis>
Body medium sized, flattened. Head in dorsal view with anterior margin weakly produced, broadly rounded, as wide as pronotum; coronal suture indistinct. Face short, depressed in profile, anteclypeus and lorum broad. Mesonotum with basal triangles indistinct. Forewing with first and third apical cells wide, second and fourth apical cells narrow, fourth cell slightly longer than half length of third, without AA and AP veins. 
<collectingCountry id="FBAAD7CE75489858B208FE93FAECFE80" box="[1313,1369,260,284]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing without RA vein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8302975E75489858B7EEFEDBFDE9FE30" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Male 
<number id="3575857975489858B62EFEDBFEA3FEF8" box="[263,278,332,356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="2.0">2</number>
S abdominal apodemes reduced, 
<number id="3575857975489858B5AFFEDBFD21FEF8" box="[646,660,332,356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="3.0">3</number>
S apodemes present and distinctive, arising from hind margin of third sternite, well sclerotized and darkly pigmented, visible even when abdomen is not cleared (
<figureCitation id="1B868BDB75489858B39CFEF8FAB2FE1B" box="[1205,1287,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1806,1829]" captionTargetBox="[200,1399,216,1736]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1783]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. a – e, Saccata insolita sp. nov.; f – i, Variolosa meni sp. nov.; j – m, Thailus rectilinea sp. nov.; n – u, Thailus versicolor sp. nov.; a, f, j, n, r, dorsal view; b, g, k, o, s, lateral view; c, h, l, p, t, anterior dorsum (crown, pronotum and mesonotum); d, i, m, q, u, face; e, abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219764/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Fig. 
<number id="3575857975489858B3C5FEF8FB42FE1B" box="[1260,1271,367,391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="1.0">1</number>
e
</figureCitation>
), pocketlike, extended to midlength of fourth sternite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8302975E75489858B7EEFE20FED1FD18" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Male genital capsule spherical, pygofer side denticulate distally, with several fine setae at lower basal angle and center of lobe; dorsal appendage movably articulated to pygofer side; ventral appendage absent. Subgenital plate broadened basally, narrowing towards apex, with 
<number id="3575857975489858B5D5FE68FCBFFD8B" box="[764,778,511,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="2.0">2</number>
macrosetae arising from angulate lareral projection at very base, with short peglike microsetae marginally. Style with second extension, preapical lobe prominent. Connective V-shaped, without central lobe. Aedeagal shaft tubular, with paired distal processes; preatrium long; gonopore subapical, ventral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBA7C4D575489858B7EEFD07FD28FD50" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8302975E75489858B7EEFD07FD28FD50" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B7EEFD07FEFBFD34" bold="true" box="[199,334,656,680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B4B7FD06FC4BFD34" box="[926,1022,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">saccatus</emphasis>
” in view of the saclike shape of the abdominal apodemes. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBA7C4D575489858B7EEFD40FF7AFC38" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8302975E75489858B7EEFD40FF7AFC38" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B7EEFD40FEF4FD6C" bold="true" box="[199,321,727,752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body shape, coloration and wing venation resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="44BDECDD75489858B320FD4FFADEFD73" authority="Dworakowska, 1971" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1971" box="[1033,1387,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Accacidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B320FD4FFBCCFD6C" box="[1033,1145,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Accacidia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E72CEAAF75489858B3ABFD40FADEFD73" author="Dworakowska" box="[1154,1387,727,751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1971) On the genera related to Tamaricella Zachv. and some other Erythroneurini (Homoptera, Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae). Suomen Hyonteistieteellinen Aikakauskirja, 37 (2), 99 - 121." type="journal article" year="1971">
Dworakowska, 
<number id="3575857975489858B21AFD40FADEFD73" box="[1331,1387,727,751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44BDECDD75489858B7BEFD6BFD9EFC88" authority="Dworakowska, 1972" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1972" box="[151,555,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lectotypella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B7BEFD6BFE97FC88" box="[151,290,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Lectotypella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E72CEAAF75489858B604FD6BFD9EFC88" author="Dworakowska" box="[301,555,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1972 b) On some Oriental genera of Typhlocybinae (Auch., Cicadellidae). Bulletin de l'Academie Polonaise des Sciences. Serie des Sciences Biologiques, 20 (2), 117 - 125." type="journal article" year="1972" yearSuffix="b">
Dworakowska, 
<number id="3575857975489858B6CAFD6BFDA8FC88" box="[483,541,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="1972.0">1972</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, male pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="44BDECDD75489858B491FD6BFAB8FC88" authority="Dworakowska, 1981" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1981" box="[952,1293,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ratjalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1C94B4C75489858B491FD6BFBA7FC88" box="[952,1042,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Ratjalia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E72CEAAF75489858B337FD6BFAB8FC88" author="Dworakowska" box="[1054,1293,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1981) Proskura gen. n. and some Erythroneurini from Souther India (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae). Reichenbachia, 19 (37), 225 - 246." type="journal article" year="1981">
Dworakowska, 
<number id="3575857975489858B3FAFD6BFAB8FC88" box="[1235,1293,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from these genera by its unique 
<typeStatus id="5C0629FC75489858B5B2FCB6FD7EFCA5" box="[667,715,801,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">type</typeStatus>
of abdominal apodemes, situated at the hind margin of the third sternite, which are pocketlike and more tridimensional than normal lamellate second sternal abdominal apodemes, subgenital plate angulate projection bearing 
<number id="3575857975489858B5A5FCF0FD2FFCE3" box="[652,666,871,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="2.0">2</number>
stout macrosetae at the very base and absence of connective central lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
